      <preface xml:id="preface">
        <title>How to Use This Book</title>
        
        <p>
          This book covers the Junior Cycle Mathematics specification, organized into 
          five strands that reflect how mathematics is structured and used.
        </p>
        
        <subsection xml:id="jc-strands">
          <title>The Five Strands</title>
          
          <ol>
            <li><p><alert>Unifying</alert> <mdash/> Mathematical thinking, reasoning, 
            communication, and problem-solving that connects all areas</p></li>
            
            <li><p><alert>Number</alert> <mdash/> Number systems, operations, factors, 
            multiples, primes, fractions, decimals, percentages, ratio, proportion</p></li>
            
            <li><p><alert>Geometry and Trigonometry</alert> <mdash/> Shapes, angles, 
            constructions, coordinate geometry, transformations, measurement</p></li>
            
            <li><p><alert>Algebra</alert> <mdash/> Expressions, equations, patterns, 
            sequences, graphing</p></li>
            
            <li><p><alert>Functions</alert> <mdash/> Relationships between quantities, 
            graphical representation, introduction to calculus concepts</p></li>
          </ol>
        </subsection>

        <subsection xml:id="study-approach">
          <title>How to Study Mathematics</title>
          
          <p>
            Mathematics is learned by doing, not by passive reading.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            For each section:
          </p>
          
          <ol>
            <li><p>Read carefully with pen and paper</p></li>
            <li><p>Work through examples step by step</p></li>
            <li><p>Write out key ideas in your own words</p></li>
            <li><p>Practice exercises until fluent</p></li>
            <li><p>Return to difficult concepts multiple times</p></li>
          </ol>
          
          <p>
            <alert>Understanding builds on understanding.</alert> Each concept prepares 
            you for the next. You cannot skip ahead without missing essential foundations.
          </p>
        </subsection>

        <subsection xml:id="exam-prep">
          <title>Preparing for Assessments</title>
          
          <p>
            Junior Cycle assessments test both:
          </p>
          
          <ul>
            <li><p><alert>Knowledge and skills</alert> <mdash/> Can you perform 
            calculations accurately and use procedures correctly?</p></li>
            
            <li><p><alert>Understanding and reasoning</alert> <mdash/> Can you explain 
            your thinking, solve unfamiliar problems, and apply mathematics in context?</p></li>
          </ul>
          
          <p>
            This book provides the theory and understanding. Practice exercises build 
            your skills. Problem-solving activities develop your reasoning.
          </p>
        </subsection>
      </preface>
    </frontmatter>

